Prof. Moshabela, who is the UKZN deputy vice-chancellor in the Research and Innovation department spoke to eNCA. #DStv403 DURBAN - The National Department of Health has announced that 80,000 doses of the Pfizer vaccine are due to expire this Thursday. The department says it's exploring strategies to increase vaccine uptake, especially among the 18–34 age group. Health expert, Professor. Mosa Moshabela is calling for vaccine equity and justice, appealing to the public not to let the doses go to waste.